1
00:00:00,793 --> 00:00:01,959
<i>Previously on</i> Fringe...

2
00:00:02,313 --> 00:00:04,935
When objects from the other universe

3
00:00:05,060 --> 00:00:07,048
cross to our side,
they have an energy.

4
00:00:08,342 --> 00:00:10,551
- Someone described it as a glimmer.
- How can I see it?

5
00:00:10,761 --> 00:00:11,969
The cortexiphan trials.

6
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:14,055
I was part of the trials
when I was a kid.

7
00:00:14,223 --> 00:00:16,390
It was a highly experimental drug.

8
00:00:16,558 --> 00:00:20,561
It might enhance certain abilities
in predisposed children.

9
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:23,520
I've never met anyone
who can do the things that you do.

10
00:00:24,775 --> 00:00:25,900
I'll go get my coat.

11
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:28,850
Please don't tell him.

12
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:40,582
You sure you don't want some soup?
Tea or coffee? To warm you up?

13
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:41,832
No, thank you.

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,025
I have trouble
keeping anything down.

15
00:00:46,548 --> 00:00:49,005
Your office told me
how busy you are.

16
00:00:49,130 --> 00:00:50,966
I really appreciate you coming.

17
00:00:52,054 --> 00:00:54,656
I'm sorry.
I keep trying to remember you.

18
00:00:54,781 --> 00:00:56,097
I understand.

19
00:00:57,025 --> 00:00:59,500
It was a long time ago.
We were just kids.

20
00:01:00,519 --> 00:01:03,584
So is that when you think
you were exposed to something?

21
00:01:03,709 --> 00:01:07,307
I've seen about
a half dozen doctors,

22
00:01:07,432 --> 00:01:08,532
specialists.

23
00:01:09,748 --> 00:01:12,723
They think it's the only explanation
that makes sense.

24
00:01:13,350 --> 00:01:14,685
Maybe I can help you.

25
00:01:16,929 --> 00:01:18,786
Look, I'm grateful

26
00:01:18,954 --> 00:01:22,039
you're doing this,
but that's not why I asked to see you.

27
00:01:22,947 --> 00:01:26,202
- I wasn't looking to make money.
- Of course. I understand.

28
00:01:27,410 --> 00:01:29,506
But if someone's responsible
for your illness,

29
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:32,247
- my firm can absolutely help...
- The last doctor I saw,

30
00:01:32,508 --> 00:01:33,942
he suggested that

31
00:01:34,067 --> 00:01:36,978
if I could find some of the other kids
we went to school with...

32
00:01:37,765 --> 00:01:39,682
If some of them
have the same symptoms,

33
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:42,768
it might help him identify
what it is that's making me sick.

34
00:01:43,908 --> 00:01:45,060
I'm sorry.

35
00:01:45,837 --> 00:01:47,857
I really don't remember names.

36
00:01:48,418 --> 00:01:49,768
It's so long ago.

37
00:01:51,294 --> 00:01:52,494
You know what?

38
00:01:54,637 --> 00:01:56,782
I do remember one boy.

39
00:01:58,738 --> 00:01:59,577
Lloyd...

40
00:02:00,269 --> 00:02:01,419
Lloyd Becker.

41
00:02:01,964 --> 00:02:03,998
He made me eat a bug
on the playground.

42
00:02:04,802 --> 00:02:06,223
I remember him.

43
00:02:06,348 --> 00:02:08,335
Lloyd Becker?

44
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:11,630
Sounds like a budding sociopath.

45
00:02:12,753 --> 00:02:13,758
Yeah, right?

46
00:02:16,148 --> 00:02:18,357
I really appreciate
you helping me out.

47
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:23,184
Neil Wilson.

48
00:02:25,551 --> 00:02:29,231
Could you make an appointment with that
oncologist over at Rhode Island General?

49
00:02:29,517 --> 00:02:32,177
- The one who always calls me "honey."
- <i>Was it Gorski?</i>

50
00:02:32,302 --> 00:02:34,228
- Gorlami...
- Dr. Gorlitsky?

51
00:02:34,353 --> 00:02:35,237
That's right.

52
00:02:35,641 --> 00:02:37,691
- I'll call him right now.
- All right, thanks.

53
00:02:37,816 --> 00:02:40,201
I should be back in 20 minutes.
Bye.

54
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:18,322
Come on!

55
00:03:23,832 --> 00:03:26,163
Hey, what's going on in there?

56
00:03:26,593 --> 00:03:27,593
Miss.

57
00:03:29,004 --> 00:03:30,156
You okay?

58
00:03:33,797 --> 00:03:35,184
Help me.

59
00:03:39,437 --> 00:03:41,512
